metatags.og:site_name: U.S. Department of Homeland Security Transportation Security Administration
metatags.og:title: Participating States and Eligible Digital IDs | Transportation Security Administration
metatags.og:description: The TSA's digital ID program allows travelers from participating states to use mobile driver's licenses or state IDs at select TSA checkpoints. These digital IDs can be added to platforms like Apple Wallet, Google Wallet, or state-specific apps. The program aims to enhance security and streamline the identity verification process. However, travelers must still carry a physical ID as a backup. You can find more details on the TSA's official page.

metatags.og:title: Mobile ID – Arkansas Department of Finance and Administration
metatags.og:description: Arkansas Mobile ID is a secure, digital version of a state-issued driver’s license or ID card that residents can access on their smartphones. It provides a convenient and contactless way to verify identity, offering enhanced security features to prevent fraud and ensure privacy.
